[I] Emulator of x86-based machines

[T] 86Box is a low level x86 emulator that runs older operating systems and
[T] software designed for IBM PC systems and compatibles from 1981 through
[T] fairly recent system designs based on the PCI bus.

[U] https://86box.net/

[A] 86Box
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/emulator
[F] CROSS

[E] opt qt6base qt6tools qt6translations
[E] opt qt5base qt5tools qt5translations

[L] GPL
[V] 6.0

[D] ea5c67f4bd1096658c1add152605791b56008d236e5883c22dc8f644 86Box-v6.0.tar.gz https://github.com/86Box/86Box/archive/v6.0/

pkginstalled qt6base && var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DUSE_QT6=ON
